						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Chōḻa, Rājakēśarivarman, Year 16 = c. 10th Century.</hi></p>						

						<p>This registers an endowment of 25 <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> of gold by a certain Koṟṟandai Poduvan and Pērangi Maṇiyan for feeding Brahmanas every, Year on the day of Svāti in Puraṭṭādi month which was the natal star Koṟṟandai Poduvan Māṟi, respectively the daughter of the first mentioned person and the wife of the latter. The gift was entrusted to the body Pāṇḍināṭṭu [= panniraṇḍu ?]-Perumakkaḷ of Tiruchcheṅgōḍu.</p>						

						<p>[Published in <hi rend="italic">SII</hi> Vol. XIII No. 261.]</p>						

						</summary>
